==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Silk-stocking
<hw>Silk"-stock`ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Wearing silk stockings
(which among men were formerly worn chiefly by the luxurious or
aristocratic); hence, elegantly dressed; aristocratic; luxurious; --
chiefly applied to men, often by way of reproach.</def></p>

<p><q>[They] will find their levees crowded with
<qex>silk-stocking</qex> gentry, but no yeomanry; an army of officers
without soldiers.</q> <rj><qau>Jefferson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silkweed</ent>⟦br⟧
